<headline>Freeze Watch issued October 17 at 4:03AM EDT until October 19 at 9:00AM EDT by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...FREEZE WATCH IN EFFECT FROM LATE TUESDAY NIGHT THROUGH
WEDNESDAY MORNING...
* WHAT...Sub-freezing temperatures as low as 30 possible and
widespread frost.
* WHERE...In North Carolina, Surry, Stokes, Rockingham, Caswell,
Wilkes and Yadkin Counties. In Virginia, Patrick, Henry,
Pittsylvania and Halifax Counties.
* WHEN...From late Tuesday night through Wednesday morning.
* IMPACTS...Frost and freeze conditions could kill crops, other
sensitive vegetation.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The expected frost and freeze will end the
growing season for the year.</description>
<instruction>Take steps now to harvest crops and protect tender plants from
the cold. Those that have in-ground sprinkler systems should drain
them and cover above-ground pipes to protect them from freezing.</instruction>
